Sentencas: Free-standing electrolyte membranes for low-temperature micro-solid oxide fuel cells (micro-SOFCs) are prepared by aerosol-assisted chemical vapor deposition (AA-CVD), a cost-effective, non-vacuum thin-film deposition technique.
Titulo: Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Membranes Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: Thin, yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) membranes (50-400 nm) as well as bilayer membranes of YSZ and gadolinia-doped ceria are prepared at temperatures of 600 degrees C and below.
Titulo: Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Membranes Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: AA-CVD, which is a gas-phase deposition method, allows for the synthesis of precursor-free crystalline layers, thereby limiting the development of tensile stress.
Titulo: Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Membranes Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: High membrane survival rates of around 90% are thus obtained.
Titulo: Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Membranes Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: The columnar structure of the electrolyte ensures high oxygen-ion conductivity and results in negligible ohmic losses.
Titulo: Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Membranes Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: Using sputtered platinum electrodes, the demonstration of a micro-SOFC based on AA-CVD electrolyte is achieved and first power density data of 166 mW cm(-2) at 410 degrees C is obtained.
Titulo: Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Membranes Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition
